<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued June 16 at 11:53PM EDT until June 17 at 4:30AM EDT by NWS Charleston</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 1215 AM EDT
FOR NORTHEASTERN RALEIGH AND SOUTHEASTERN FAYETTE COUNTIES...
At 1152 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 8 miles northwest
of Sandstone, moving southeast at 15 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind damage to
roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Piney View, Stanaford, Prosperity, Bradley, Meadow Bridge and
Thurmond.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.00 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
